OL,3,CSynagogue's 150 year anniversary hopes
OL,4,Cto unite communities
OL,6,FThe oldest surviving synagogue
OL,7,Fbuilding in Manchester is celebrating
OL,8,F150 years as a place of worship.
OL,10,FThe iconic building in Cheetham Hill
OL,11,Fopened on 6 May 1874 and is now home
OL,12,Fto the Manchester Jewish Museum.
OL,14,FAlex Cropper is Curator at the
OL,15,FManchester Jewish Museum, she said
OL,17,F"It's important to know about the
OL,18,Fdiverse communities that make up
OL,19,FManchester today and make Manchester
OL,20,Fwho it is and the Jewish community is
OL,21,Fjust one of these stories"
